benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/timeline - Retrieve account timeline

covered: Valid Request: Multiple successful retrieval scenarios (no params, parallel, audit=FULL/MINIMAL, combined) validate expected 200 behavior and response shape.
Empty Response: Scenarios for accounts with no bundles/invoices/payments (TC06, TC17) cover empty-data responses.
Query Parameters: Positive and negative tests for parallel and audit parameters (valid values, invalid values) and combined usage are present (TC02-TC05, TC27, TC28).
Authorization: Authentication-related error scenarios are present (missing token and invalid token -> 401) (TC10, TC11).

Error Handling / Edge Cases: Invalid accountId format (400), non-existent account (404), service/db failures (503/500), security injection/XSS checks, and other edge cases like max/min UUID lengths are included (TC08, TC09, TC12, TC13, TC14, TC15, TC18, TC19).
Performance & Concurrency: Stress and performance-related scenarios exist (large datasets, concurrent requests, timeout/long-running, recovery from transient network errors) (TC07, TC20, TC25, TC26).
Regression/Backward Compatibility: Regression checks for previously fixed bugs and backward compatibility casing test are present (TC21, TC22, TC23).
gaps: Pagination: No tests for pagination behavior or limits when responses are large (e.g., page size, next/prev links, offset/limit semantics).
Caching Behavior / Response Headers: No scenarios validate caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control, Last-Modified) or conditional GET behavior (304 responses).
Rate Limiting / Throttling: No tests for rate limiting or API throttling (429 responses) under high request rates.
Authorization: While 401 cases are covered, there is no test for forbidden access (403) or role/permission-based access control.
Content Negotiation & Headers: No tests verify Accept/Content-Type handling, or that the response produces application/json and appropriate charset headers.
Pagination + Performance Interaction: Although large dataset performance is covered, there is no test combining pagination with performance or parallel fetching effects on paged data.
Response Schema Validation Depth: Tests assert a valid AccountTimeline is returned but do not enumerate/validate all required fields, types, and nested object contracts (strong schema assertions).
Error payload format: While status codes are covered for many errors, there is limited validation of structured error body format and consistent error codes/messages across scenarios.
recommendations: Add pagination tests: include page size limits, offset/limit or page tokens, behavior at boundaries (last page empty), and interactions with parallel fetching.
Add caching and conditional GET tests: verify ETag, Cache-Control, Last-Modified headers, 304 Not Modified behavior, and cache header correctness for timeline responses.
Add rate-limiting tests: simulate high request rates to validate 429 responses, backoff behavior, and any Retry-After header support.
Expand authorization tests: include 403 forbidden scenarios (insufficient privileges), role-based access checks, and token scope variations.
Validate headers and content negotiation: assert response Content-Type is application/json, proper charset, and behavior when Accept is unsupported.
Strengthen schema validation: add tests that validate all required fields, types, and nested elements of AccountTimeline per the API definition rather than only "valid object" high-level assertions.
Error body consistency: assert structured error response fields (code, message, details) for 400/404/500/503 cases to ensure clients can programmatically handle errors.
Combine pagination with performance and parallelism: test large paginated timelines with parallel=true to catch partial/missing data bugs under realistic load.
Add rate-limited and cache-aware performance tests to measure real-world behavior when caching and throttling are active.
